subSubSection.paragraph:
Metasoma (
Figs. 1, 2, 4
) 4.2–4.6 times longer than wide; T 1 slightly wider than long, T 2 –T 5 distinctly so, T 6 3.0– 3.5 times longer than wide; T 1 –T 5 with broad longitudinal furrow laterally (
Fig. 2
), sometimes weaker in posterior tergites; costae of T 1 strong but not more strongly impressed around base of horn; horn coriarious except for smooth and shining tip (
Fig. 4
); T 6 entirely coriarious-punctate, with some longitudinal carinulae; anterior lens-shaped area of S 2 often strongly angular and tooth-like in profile (
Fig. 1
).
